  "prompt": "Can I apply for a PR in Australia while I am studying in Australia for a masters course on a student visa 573? I have met the criteria of 65 points.",
  "response": "Yes, you can apply for Permanent Residency (PR) in Australia while studying on a student visa. Here are some key points to consider:\n\n1. Points Test Eligibility:\n- Having 65 points is a good start\n- More points can improve your chances\n- Points can come from age, education, work experience, English language skills, etc.\n\n2. Potential Pathways:\n- Skilled Independent Visa (Subclass 189)\n- Skilled Nominated Visa (Subclass 190)\n- Skilled Regional Visa (Subclass 491)\n\n3. Requirements:\n- Complete your masters course\n- Obtain a positive skills assessment in your occupation\n- Meet English language requirements\n- Have relevant work experience\n- Age limit (generally under 45)\n\n4. Benefits of Applying During Study:\n- Already in Australia\n- Can potentially claim additional points for Australian study\n- Familiar with local environment\n\n5. Recommended Steps:\n- Check your occupation's eligibility on the skilled occupation list\n- Get skills assessment\n- Take IELTS/PTE to maximize points\n- Consult a registered migration agent for personalized advice\n\nRemember that immigration rules can change, so always verify the latest information with the Department of Home Affairs.",
